Link added, "Rufus King High School". Political career updated. Additional information is given for the 2018 congressional race and endorsements earned by Bryce. Edit: Randy Bryce was born in Milwaukee, not South Milwaukee. He was raised by his biological mother and stepfather who adopted him at 5 years old. Citations added to reflect this. Additional information included reflecting high school education and U.S. army service.
Bryce was raised on the Southside of Milwaukee. Cancer diagnosis resulted in a career in the building trades.

Early life: capitalized Ironworker, U.S. Army Veteran, and Activist. Including that Bryce's race was the first to ever unionize in U.S. history (fact). Early Life: Randy Bryce was NOT born in South Milwaukee, he was born on the Southside of Milwaukee. Including notes to show that Bryce WAS adopted by his stepfather, Richard Bryce. Randy went to Rufus King High School in Milwaukee and enlisted as a soldier in the army. Randy never finished college due to a testicular cancer diagnosis.
